---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Doghouse Cafe"
  description="About Doghouse Cafe and the people building it."
>
  <div class="about-page">
    <a class="about-back" href="/">&larr; Back to Doghouse Cafe</a>

    <section class="about-hero">
      <h1>About Doghouse Cafe</h1>

      <p>
        Doghouse Cafe is a community for real-world engineering: production failures,
        weird edge cases, debugging paths, partial answers, and the gap between
        &ldquo;it should work&rdquo; and what actually happens.
      </p>

      <p>
        This is not polished thought leadership. It is a place for builders,
        operators, and contributors to share what they have actually seen,
        tried, broken, fixed, or still do not fully understand.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Guiding idea</h2>
      <p>
        If it should work... but doesn&rsquo;t - it belongs here.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Who&rsquo;s building it?</h2>

      <div class="team-grid">
        <article class="team-card founder">
          <div class="profile-bg"></div>
          <div class="avatar-ring">
            <img class="team-avatar" src="/assets/team/matt.webp" alt="Matt McGowan" />
          </div>

          <h3>Matt McGowan</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Co-Founder,<br />Infrastructure Lead</p>

          <p class="team-bio">
            Matt is Co-Founder of Dog House Cafe, leading platform direction and technical strategy. With experience across infrastructure, reliability, and large-scale systems, he focuses on translating real-world operational lessons into practical insights for the community.
          </p>

          <div class="team-links">
            <a class="team-link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/matthewcmcgowan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              LinkedIn
            </a>
            <div class="team-affiliations">
              <a class="team-affiliation-link" href="#">
                NullorNaN Systems LLC
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="team-card founder">
          <div class="profile-bg"></div>
          <div class="avatar-ring">
            <img class="team-avatar" src="/assets/team/dani.webp" alt="Dani Perteet" />
          </div>

          <h3>Dani Perteet</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Co-Founder,<br />Head of Community &amp; Growth</p>

          <p class="team-bio">
            Dani is Co-Founder of Dog House Cafe, leading community growth and partnerships. With a background in hosting and operations, they bring a practical, systems-first perspective and focus on connecting builders who have worked through real-world infrastructure challenges.
          </p>

          <div class="team-links">
            <a class="team-link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/dani-perteet-76439421/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              LinkedIn
            </a>
            <div class="team-affiliations">
              <a class="team-affiliation-link" href="https://speedmax.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Speedmax LLC
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="team-card dev">
          <div class="profile-bg"></div>
          <div class="avatar-ring">
            <span class="guest-avatar-icon" role="img" aria-label="Guest Contributors"></span>
          </div>
          <h3>Contributors</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Internal &amp; External Contributors</p>
          <p class="team-bio">
            Doghouse Cafe grows through contributors - builders, operators, and
            debuggers who share real-world experiences, edge cases, and lessons
            learned in production. Some contribute regularly. Others drop in with
            a single insight. Both matter.
          </p>

          <a class="team-link" href="https://community.doghouse.cafe" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Join the Community
          </a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
